Shares of the following companies
may have  unusual (JCI)  moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The Jakarta Composite index rose less than 0.1 percent to
3,795.44.  PT Bhakti Capital Indonesia (BCAP)  : The brokerage bought
99.9 percent of PT Jamindo General Insurance for 40 billion
rupiah ($4.4 million), Bisnis Indonesia reported, citing Bhakti
Capital President Director Darma Putra. Bhakti Capital rose 12
percent to 560 rupiah.  PT Energi Mega Persada (ENRG)  : Cnooc Ltd. sold a
subsidiary that holds about 36.7 percent of an oil and gas field
production contract in Indonesia for $212 million, according to
a statement to PR Newswire. The buyer was EMP International
(BVI) Ltd., it said. Energi Mega, the parent company of EMP
International, fell 1.1 percent to 177 rupiah.  PT Timah (TINS)  : Tin futures rose for a fourth straight
day, adding 0.4 percent to $19,300 a metric ton in after-hours
trading in London. Timah, Indonesiaâ€™s largest tin producer, was
